wikipedia_page.main: Albert J. Prince (born 1895, date of death unknown) was an English footballer. His regular position was as a forward. He was born in Smallthorne, Staffordshire. He played for Manchester United and Stafford Rangers

response: Albert Prince (November 17, 1825 – July 18, 1875) was an Ontario lawyer and political figure. He represented Essex in the Legislative Assembly of Ontario as a Liberal member from 1871 to 1874.
